cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of automatic pancreas segmentation in radiology images using deep learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture and recurrent neural network-based approach for pancreas segmentation, which involves designing a domain-specific network and contextual learning. Hence, it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
